-- Ex-Sun Hung Kai Properties co-chairman sentenced to 5 years for graft 
-- By Lizzie Ko and Donny Kwok
-- Mon Dec 22, 2014 10:18PM EST
-- None



HONG KONG, Dec 23 (Reuters) - Former co-chairman of Hong Kong-listed developer Sun Hung Kai Properties Ltd <0016.HK>, Thomas Kwok, was sentenced to five years in jail and a HK$500,000 ($64,440) fine on Tuesday for corruption in the city's highest profile graft case.

Billionaire Thomas Kwok, 63, was found guilty of one count of conspiracy to commit misconduct in public office. His younger brother, Raymond Kwok, also co-chairman of the city's largest developer, was cleared of all charges. [ID:nL3N0U32OW]